Heh I wish I could get my orum back from this spell. If you are resting in between every kill you are killing at a snails pace. And I dont ever have enough spell slots to mem this in addition to a regular mez. 
<br />

<br />
IMO when you really need an unresistable mez, just click Nightmare Stasis... The refresh time on that is on 30 minutes...use it more and save you orum!</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
A lot of people are confused by this spell's description. The resting they refer to has nothing to do with out of combat resting states. It's simply describing the recast timer on the spell. The length of the recast timer is not affected by your combat status. There is no reason to rest between every kill. Try it out again, you might really like it, I know I do, it's basically the new rapture. 1.5 second cast time, less mana cost than bewilderment, -110 chromatic resist check, what's not to love? Sure it has a 90 second recast timer, but nothing beats it for locking something down fast, safely, and reliably.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
