			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is another tool.  It is ridiculously reliable on any non-raid content -- I've never had it resisted on an XP mob, period.
<br />

<br />
I use it more often to &quot;pick off&quot; creatures for charming than I use it for other reasons.  Flash, Tash, Charm produces a &quot;get a pet for free&quot; charm, that is ready to fight in 45 seconds or so -- enough time to haste it, gear it up, mark NPC it, mem tiny companion, shrink it, and by the next mob your pet is blendering.
<br />

<br />
I can also use it when playing the ninja and bypassing content.
<br />

<br />
Sure, you can only use it every 90 seconds.  And it eats up a spell slot.  But it is quite useful regardless.
<br />

<br />
You can also save it for when your normal mez is resisted -- at 1.5 seconds, it is as easy to channel as your PBAOE mez, and it is very unlikely to get resisted.
<br />

<br />
A standard spell load:
<br />
1 Root or Whatever
<br />
2 Charm
<br />
3 Draconic Rune
<br />
4 PBAOE mez
<br />
5 Tash
<br />
6 Mez
<br />
7 Spin
<br />
8 Whatever (DoT, Recursion, Ward, or anything useful)
<br />
9 Flash
<br />

<br />
And yes, I'd love a 10th spell gem.  :)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
