			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">They are right about lining up the pet, but I'll make a few tips that they take for granted.  First, you want to have a fast sow on.  We're talking druid's wolf form, flight of eagles, etc.  Then pull from max range-ish.  These give you room to maneuver at the end.  You run past the mob a little bit and turn around.  Then strafe (Ctrl+Left/Right Arrow keys) to guide the mob in to your pet.  I usually have such a big jump on the mob that this is extraordinarily easy.  When I do this, the pet always pulls the mob off easily.  Though it is possible, I suppose, that some of the aggro reducing AA's may have some impact.  The other possibility I can think of is if you are not soloing and are impacted by the rule of four (if that is still valid?)  That could definitely mess up the aggro.  
<br />

<br />
Sunamae
<br />
7th Hammer</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
