				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>nillitik wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Maybe I'll try the spamming stun thing....I thought I was, guess I'll give it another shot. 
<br />

<br />
Another problem I've been running into is attempting to keep my pet rooted, maybe once I get that AA from the new expansion it'll be better, but it seems my pet's root always dies anyway.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
To be clear, this is exactly how i do it:
<br />

<br />
-Pull with tash from MAX RANGE
<br />
-Run immediately back to pet and run behind him a bit.
<br />
-Start spamming stun, when mob is in range, you start casting
<br />
-Pet Attack while stun is casting
<br />
-Click slow stick after stun lands
<br />
-Cripple is a nice folow up here
<br />
-Spin Stun
<br />
-Root
<br />
-Spin Stun
<br />
-Min Phobiate / root / nothing
<br />
-More Spins and roots til its deaded.
<br />

<br />

<br />
As for keeping your own pet rooted, I wouldnt count on that happening much. In a way thats why reverse charming is a lot safer than ally charm. With reverse charming the biggest threat is always rooted. leaving you at worst a mortally wounded, vanilla mob to deal with during pet breaks. Not a big deal.<br />_________________<br />&quot;Those who stand with me shall be my brothers.&quot; -Vizier
<br />
<a href="http://reborninfire.org" target="_blank">http://reborninfire.org</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
